# wabox-bot heartbeat — crontab example.
#
# Runs a standing prompt for ONE conversation every 30 minutes between 08:00 and
# 22:00, and lets the agent decide whether to message you (it replies with the
# NOOP sentinel when there's nothing worth saying — see standing-prompt.txt).
#
# Install with `crontab -e` and paste the line below, after editing:
#   - SLUG   : the conversation to speak into. Find it with
#                wabox-bot state --json \
#                  | jq -r '.conversations[] | "\(.slug)\t\(.conv_key)\t\(.last_message.text_preview // "")"'
#              and copy the slug of the chat you want the heartbeat to post to.
#   - paths  : point at your wabox-bot install and your standing prompt file.
#
# `|| [ $? -eq 5 ]` turns the NOOP suppression exit code (5) back into success,
# so a quiet heartbeat is not logged/alerted as a cron failure. A real failure
# (usage 1, lock busy 3, timeout 124) still surfaces.
#
# cron runs each line under /bin/sh with a minimal PATH — use absolute paths.

SLUG=REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_SLUG
*/30 8-22 * * * /home/you/.local/bin/wabox-bot prompt "$SLUG" "$(cat /home/you/.config/wabox-bot/standing-prompt.txt)" >> /home/you/.local/state/wabox-bot/heartbeat.log 2>&1 || [ $? -eq 5 ]
